WEBVTT

00:00:05.571 --> 00:00:06.971
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

00:00:06.971 --> 00:00:08.511
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

00:00:09.841 --> 00:00:10.841
I will now have to...

00:00:10.911 --> 00:00:12.011
(Episode 12)

00:00:12.081 --> 00:00:14.481
- let it become a part of...
- Hold on!

00:00:14.481 --> 00:00:15.481
(Happy 40th Anniversary!)

00:00:20.151 --> 00:00:21.181
What's going on?

00:00:23.321 --> 00:00:26.591
Hey, what do you think you're doing?
I was giving an important speech.

00:00:27.061 --> 00:00:28.831
Well, the thing is...

00:00:29.161 --> 00:00:30.191
Congratulations.

00:00:30.191 --> 00:00:32.231
- I said congratulations to him.
- What?

00:00:32.701 --> 00:00:36.971
Congratulations to you
Happy 40th anniversary to you

00:00:37.031 --> 00:00:38.271
(Happy 40th Anniversary!)

00:00:38.341 --> 00:00:42.171
The 40th anniversary of
Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic

00:00:42.341 --> 00:00:43.511
- All together now.
- Hey.

00:00:43.571 --> 00:00:44.571
Congratulations

00:00:45.981 --> 00:00:47.781
- A round of applause!
- What's gotten into you?

00:00:47.841 --> 00:00:49.181
Congratulations!

00:00:49.181 --> 00:00:51.311
Go, Dae Han! Go, Korea!

00:00:51.981 --> 00:00:54.751
Congratulations, Jeong Han.
And congratulations to you, sir.

00:00:55.991 --> 00:00:56.991
Hi, Jin Ah.

00:00:57.591 --> 00:00:58.821
Our very own Director Gong.

00:00:59.361 --> 00:01:01.661
Hey, what do you think you're doing?

00:01:01.731 --> 00:01:04.831
This is fantastic!
Congratulations, I mean it.

00:01:04.891 --> 00:01:07.831
Are you going to let go or not?
I'm serious.

00:01:07.901 --> 00:01:11.631
Well then, enjoy yourselves!
Please eat and drink your fill.

00:01:12.771 --> 00:01:16.271
- I'm not letting go. Come here.
- Hey, let go of me!

00:01:16.341 --> 00:01:17.771
(Happy 40th Anniversary!)

00:01:18.341 --> 00:01:19.411
You've got to be kidding me.

00:01:20.611 --> 00:01:23.311
What's with you? Let go.
What kind of stunt is this?

00:01:23.381 --> 00:01:25.581
This is urgent.
Jeong Han, about your move...

00:01:25.651 --> 00:01:29.291
- I'm moving. I already told you.
- Don't.

00:01:29.351 --> 00:01:30.421
You don't want me to move out?

00:01:30.851 --> 00:01:34.261
- What's this weird plan? Seriously.
- Look, the thing is...

00:01:34.521 --> 00:01:36.261
I got a call.

00:01:37.191 --> 00:01:39.561
Right. You're getting a call, too.

00:01:39.961 --> 00:01:41.031
Who could this be?

00:01:42.431 --> 00:01:43.501
Hello?

00:01:44.471 --> 00:01:47.301
I'm sorry? "Human Theater?"

00:01:47.301 --> 00:01:48.371
Just say yes.

00:01:50.041 --> 00:01:54.841
- Yes, so you want to film us?
- You can do it. Just say yes.

00:01:55.951 --> 00:01:56.981
I see.

00:01:56.981 --> 00:02:00.881
- I really have no interest in...
- Yes, we're interested. We are.

00:02:00.951 --> 00:02:02.751
- Hey.
- After consulting Director Yang,

00:02:02.751 --> 00:02:04.351
- Seriously.
- we'll call you back.

00:02:04.421 --> 00:02:07.691
- This is ridiculous.
- Sure. Thank you. Bye now.

00:02:09.991 --> 00:02:11.901
You do whatever you want, don't you?
Unbelievable.

00:02:11.961 --> 00:02:13.961
Hey, it's for a whole month!

00:02:14.201 --> 00:02:17.671
It will be broadcast nationwide
for an entire month!

00:02:17.901 --> 00:02:21.401
You know how high the ratings are
for a show like that, don't you?

00:02:21.601 --> 00:02:23.211
So what?

00:02:23.211 --> 00:02:25.381
What do you mean?
We have to do the show!

00:02:25.441 --> 00:02:27.281
Knock yourself out.

00:02:27.741 --> 00:02:29.251
- Unbelievable.
- Hey, listen.

00:02:29.251 --> 00:02:31.111
We have been friends
for almost 50 years.

00:02:31.181 --> 00:02:34.551
We're the icons of Onjeong Market,
facing each other for 40 years,

00:02:34.621 --> 00:02:36.351
and we're President and VP
of the Merchants Association.

00:02:36.421 --> 00:02:38.721
Give me a break, 50 years
of friendship, my foot!

00:02:38.721 --> 00:02:40.591
We fight every time we meet.

00:02:40.621 --> 00:02:45.061
Besides, if we do that show,
everyone will know we're enemies.

00:02:45.131 --> 00:02:47.601
- Get a grip.
- I’ve come to my senses.

00:02:47.601 --> 00:02:48.631
And no one will know.

00:02:48.801 --> 00:02:51.471
Come on, Jeong Han.
This is my one big wish.

00:02:51.631 --> 00:02:55.171
Come on, an opportunity like this
is once in a lifetime.

00:02:55.171 --> 00:02:59.411
You want to be famous, make it big.
You want to get popular...

00:02:59.481 --> 00:03:02.081
so you can run for city council
and win.

00:03:02.411 --> 00:03:05.751
But listen,
that's your problem, not mine.

00:03:06.051 --> 00:03:07.281
Am I wrong?

00:03:07.281 --> 00:03:08.381
What are you doing, Jeong Han?

00:03:09.721 --> 00:03:11.591
- Just go already.
- Let's just do it.

00:03:11.651 --> 00:03:12.721
Go on, get out of here.

00:03:13.591 --> 00:03:14.891
The ratings could hit 30 percent!

00:03:15.461 --> 00:03:17.661
- Go away.
- Oh, dear.

00:03:19.601 --> 00:03:22.771
- What's gotten into him?
- He's just spouting nonsense.

00:03:23.301 --> 00:03:26.671
I was going to tell him I'm moving,
but I missed my chance.

00:03:26.741 --> 00:03:28.511
Tell him when you introduce
Dr. Jo Taek Hwan...

00:03:28.511 --> 00:03:29.871
when he stops by to say hi.

00:03:30.311 --> 00:03:31.911
You think?
Okay, I guess I'll have to.

00:03:32.611 --> 00:03:35.041
- Hey, let's get back to the clinic.
- Right.

00:03:36.481 --> 00:03:37.481
Yes, honey.

00:03:38.411 --> 00:03:40.551
I just popped out to see Hyun Bin.

00:03:41.021 --> 00:03:44.851
I only meant to drop off some side dishes,
but he took the morning off.

00:03:46.091 --> 00:03:47.421
So we came out
for some tea together.

00:03:47.761 --> 00:03:49.261
Okay, let's talk about it at home.

00:03:53.761 --> 00:03:55.271
The side dishes were just an excuse,
weren't they?

00:03:56.731 --> 00:03:59.141
I came to say sorry for pushing you
into that blind date...

00:03:59.771 --> 00:04:01.501
and also to properly ask you
for a favor.

00:04:02.441 --> 00:04:05.881
When I heard Councilor Hwang's daughter
went to your office,

00:04:06.081 --> 00:04:07.441
you have no idea how shocked I was.

00:04:08.011 --> 00:04:10.981
You were more shocked
that I like someone, weren’t you?

00:04:11.681 --> 00:04:12.721
Not really.

00:04:13.251 --> 00:04:15.251
Didn't you just make that up
to turn her down?

00:04:15.991 --> 00:04:16.991
You're right.

00:04:17.951 --> 00:04:18.961
But...

00:04:20.661 --> 00:04:22.631
what if I really did have
someone I liked,

00:04:22.891 --> 00:04:24.961
or was dating? What would you do?

00:04:26.231 --> 00:04:28.061
I'd insist that you introduce me
to her right away.

00:04:28.571 --> 00:04:31.431
I'd have to be the first to meet her
and see what she's like.

00:04:32.571 --> 00:04:33.941
I figured you'd say that.

00:04:34.401 --> 00:04:35.411
So,

00:04:35.941 --> 00:04:37.971
for you to go that far
to get out of it,

00:04:38.271 --> 00:04:39.781
was Councilor Hwang's daughter
really that bad?

00:04:40.481 --> 00:04:43.751
I heard she really liked you.

00:04:44.381 --> 00:04:46.751
You should've met her one more time.

00:04:48.151 --> 00:04:50.191
Meeting her again...

00:04:52.821 --> 00:04:55.331
isn't going to help my father.

00:04:59.631 --> 00:05:00.961
But, Hyun Bin.

00:05:01.731 --> 00:05:02.801
This arrangement...

00:05:03.501 --> 00:05:05.741
wasn't just for your father's sake.

00:05:06.671 --> 00:05:08.441
If you found someone special,

00:05:09.071 --> 00:05:11.941
I thought you might not leave Korea
in a year.

00:05:13.211 --> 00:05:15.781
I want you to stop drifting,
meet someone good,

00:05:16.581 --> 00:05:19.451
and finally put down
some roots here.

00:05:27.061 --> 00:05:29.831
Gong Ju Ah, hurry up.
The presentation is all set up.

00:05:31.261 --> 00:05:33.801
Where's Director Yang? Didn't he say
he'd watch us rehearse?

00:05:33.861 --> 00:05:34.861
An external meeting?

00:05:35.531 --> 00:05:37.071
He hasn't even come in to work yet.

00:05:38.031 --> 00:05:39.041
Oh my goodness.

00:05:39.501 --> 00:05:42.341
Wait, what about yesterday?
Did he return after the blind date?

00:05:42.941 --> 00:05:44.911
- No.
- No way.

00:05:45.171 --> 00:05:50.011
- So he was out all night?
- What are you even thinking?

00:05:50.181 --> 00:05:53.151
I can't believe him.

00:05:53.151 --> 00:05:54.851
He said he liked you so much,

00:05:54.851 --> 00:05:58.691
but things get a little difficult,
and he just jumps to another woman?

00:05:58.761 --> 00:06:00.261
That's enough.

00:06:00.621 --> 00:06:01.621
Wait a second.

00:06:02.531 --> 00:06:05.901
Could this be one
of those "make you jealous" ploys?

00:06:06.001 --> 00:06:09.701
Come on, do you really think
he's that childish? Seriously.

00:06:10.001 --> 00:06:11.701
You're unbelievable.

00:06:14.271 --> 00:06:16.071
That was Kim So Hye. She said...

00:06:16.071 --> 00:06:17.611
Director Yang went straight
to the briefing room.

00:06:17.941 --> 00:06:18.941
Let's go.

00:06:27.621 --> 00:06:31.591
We'll return to the brand's essence
and revive its original mood.

00:06:31.721 --> 00:06:34.221
We'll also expand
to the sensibilities...

00:06:34.221 --> 00:06:36.531
and direction this era demands.

00:06:37.131 --> 00:06:39.061
Next is our design concept.

00:06:39.361 --> 00:06:41.561
Our FG premium line is prestigious,

00:06:41.561 --> 00:06:44.101
while embodying a sense
of freedom...

00:06:44.171 --> 00:06:46.601
- and sophistication...
- Hold on a second.

00:06:48.641 --> 00:06:51.771
I think the opening
is a little flat.

00:06:54.681 --> 00:06:57.981
What exactly do you mean by "flat?"

00:06:58.351 --> 00:06:59.681
It's not memorable.

00:07:00.681 --> 00:07:03.191
I think we need
more impactful storytelling.

00:07:03.391 --> 00:07:07.321
This final version incorporates
all of your feedback.

00:07:07.421 --> 00:07:11.731
I know, but I didn't feel that way
when I read the script.

00:07:11.961 --> 00:07:15.331
But the opening isn't grabbing me,

00:07:15.431 --> 00:07:17.731
so it's hard to focus
on the rest of the concept.

00:07:18.801 --> 00:07:20.271
Vice President,
what are your thoughts?

00:07:20.541 --> 00:07:22.071
I thought it was fine.

00:07:22.841 --> 00:07:24.011
The designs are great.

00:07:24.941 --> 00:07:28.181
Director Yang, isn't it unreasonable
to change it now?

00:07:32.681 --> 00:07:33.751
If I were on the judging panel,

00:07:35.991 --> 00:07:37.651
I'd reject this proposal.

00:07:42.431 --> 00:07:43.691
Let's change the entire structure.

00:07:43.931 --> 00:07:47.431
You said it was good before,
but now you want to change it?

00:07:47.601 --> 00:07:50.201
It's natural to change something
you're not satisfied with.

00:07:50.571 --> 00:07:54.801
I see. So you just replace things
you're not happy with?

00:07:54.871 --> 00:07:58.071
Why waste time on something
that has no future?

00:08:01.181 --> 00:08:04.481
Those two seem to be getting
a little emotional.

00:08:04.551 --> 00:08:07.151
The Vice President will handle it.

00:08:08.021 --> 00:08:10.321
This isn't about the presentation,
is it?

00:08:10.651 --> 00:08:13.821
Of course not.
That's clearly a lovers' quarrel.

00:08:14.291 --> 00:08:18.091
If you planned to change it,
you shouldn't have praised it then.

00:08:18.161 --> 00:08:22.231
Your praise got our hopes up,
but because one thing's wrong,

00:08:22.331 --> 00:08:23.971
you want to change
everything just like that?

00:08:25.001 --> 00:08:28.201
So what? Once I make up my mind,
I can't change it ever again?

00:08:28.201 --> 00:08:29.211
What...

00:08:33.241 --> 00:08:34.841
Seriously...

00:08:59.141 --> 00:09:01.041
She has no idea
what I’m really feeling.

00:09:08.111 --> 00:09:11.851
- See? We should've gotten burgers.
- But lately...

00:09:14.451 --> 00:09:16.721
There you guys are!

00:09:21.861 --> 00:09:25.061
- Do you mind if we join you?
- Have a seat.

00:09:26.731 --> 00:09:28.601
Hey, Pro Kim.

00:09:28.931 --> 00:09:31.271
I'm sorry if I upset you.

00:09:31.831 --> 00:09:36.311
Not at all, Director.
I came up short. I'll do it again.

00:09:36.641 --> 00:09:39.111
That's right. We still have time,

00:09:39.281 --> 00:09:40.411
so let's try to revise it.

00:09:41.611 --> 00:09:44.711
I'm so sorry about earlier,
Vice President.

00:09:45.011 --> 00:09:46.051
Sorry? For what?

00:09:46.321 --> 00:09:49.751
I get it, Ju Ah.
You gave it your all...

00:09:49.821 --> 00:09:54.461
and someone changes their mind
just like that. I'd be mad too.

00:09:55.091 --> 00:09:57.631
So are you going to apologize to me
or not?

00:09:57.761 --> 00:09:59.461
Fine. I'm sorry.

00:10:02.271 --> 00:10:04.501
Ju Ah, just let it go.

00:10:04.771 --> 00:10:07.041
What's the big deal
about changing a presentation?

00:10:07.101 --> 00:10:09.341
People even change partners
when they're not happy...

00:10:09.541 --> 00:10:13.441
- and go on endless blind dates.
- Please, just stop.

00:10:14.841 --> 00:10:17.181
Oh, right. A blind date?

00:10:18.181 --> 00:10:20.751
So Hye, do you remember
that blind date I turned down?

00:10:21.681 --> 00:10:23.851
- You mean my brother?
- Yes.

00:10:24.391 --> 00:10:28.931
Your charming older brother.
I think I might go on it after all.

00:10:29.191 --> 00:10:32.261
I thought you weren't going.
Did you change your mind?

00:10:33.531 --> 00:10:37.001
People can change their minds,
can't they?

00:10:37.831 --> 00:10:39.101
Right, Director Yang?

00:10:40.671 --> 00:10:41.671
Yes.

00:10:44.011 --> 00:10:45.371
I thought you said...

00:10:45.371 --> 00:10:46.841
those "make you jealous" ploys
were childish.

00:10:47.341 --> 00:10:48.911
That's not what this is.

00:10:57.991 --> 00:10:59.261
Woo Jae, what do you think?

00:10:59.521 --> 00:11:03.191
Out of all the places we saw today,
I liked the last one the best.

00:11:03.291 --> 00:11:04.291
Me too.

00:11:04.761 --> 00:11:06.431
See? We're totally on the same page.

00:11:07.501 --> 00:11:11.201
The price was low for the area
and it was well-maintained, right?

00:11:11.331 --> 00:11:14.471
Your and Ju Ah's commute
would be almost an hour shorter too.

00:11:14.871 --> 00:11:18.211
The subway station is close,
and lots of bus routes, right?

00:11:18.271 --> 00:11:19.511
The walking trail was nice, too.

00:11:19.881 --> 00:11:22.911
- We could go for walks to exercise.
- Sure.

00:11:23.251 --> 00:11:25.851
Let's ask the rest of the family,
and if they're all okay with it,

00:11:25.921 --> 00:11:27.281
we'll take that place.

00:11:28.581 --> 00:11:30.821
This is Ju Ah's store.

00:11:32.191 --> 00:11:34.291
Now Mom is the model for this brand?

00:11:34.291 --> 00:11:35.361
Let's go take a look.

00:11:35.661 --> 00:11:36.661
Sounds good.

00:11:37.831 --> 00:11:39.301
- Welcome.
- Hello.

00:11:39.361 --> 00:11:40.501
Hello.

00:11:40.731 --> 00:11:43.801
Grandma, I have some allowance left.
How about I buy you an outfit?

00:11:50.171 --> 00:11:51.171
This one...

00:11:51.671 --> 00:11:53.281
This is perfect.

00:11:53.611 --> 00:11:56.251
You should be the model for this,
Grandma, not Mom.

00:11:58.011 --> 00:12:00.281
Let's get one for your dad
and one for your uncle.

00:12:00.621 --> 00:12:03.421
That's true.
They'll need more clothes for work.

00:12:04.291 --> 00:12:05.551
Are you looking for
a particular style?

00:12:05.621 --> 00:12:10.091
Yes, something comfortable
and clean-cut for men.

00:12:10.261 --> 00:12:13.131
Okay, then this collection over here
would be a great fit.

00:12:18.401 --> 00:12:19.641
How about something like this?

00:12:19.901 --> 00:12:23.111
It's lightweight and it wears well,
so it's very comfortable.

00:12:23.171 --> 00:12:24.171
What do you think?

00:12:24.441 --> 00:12:25.811
I think they'd look great.

00:12:29.711 --> 00:12:31.911
Hello? The real estate agency?

00:12:31.911 --> 00:12:32.921
Yes, hello.

00:12:33.681 --> 00:12:37.091
Could you give me a call
when Director Gong's house sells?

00:12:38.191 --> 00:12:41.761
It's already been sold?
Are you serious?

00:12:42.731 --> 00:12:46.331
So the police chief's family
is moving in.

00:12:46.831 --> 00:12:51.031
That's wonderful. Thank you.
I'll be in touch. Bye.

00:13:03.181 --> 00:13:04.281
What are you up to?

00:13:04.751 --> 00:13:06.321
I was just watching
to see if Dong Suk would show up.

00:13:07.481 --> 00:13:08.881
You scared me.

00:13:09.351 --> 00:13:11.091
You asked to see me,
so why are you hiding?

00:13:11.251 --> 00:13:14.321
No, it's not that.
It's just, when I see you...

00:13:16.191 --> 00:13:18.991
What? You have to take a crap
when you see me?

00:13:18.991 --> 00:13:20.561
That's such a horrible thing to say.

00:13:20.631 --> 00:13:24.331
- It's a psychogenic stomachache.
- What's that?

00:13:24.401 --> 00:13:27.971
When I see you, I get so stressed
that my stomach starts to hurt.

00:13:28.671 --> 00:13:30.711
- You look perfectly fine to me.
- What?

00:13:32.511 --> 00:13:34.741
You're right. You know what?
My house was sold.

00:13:35.111 --> 00:13:37.651
I'm moving, and now I realize
I won't have to see you anymore.

00:13:37.911 --> 00:13:39.821
And it really doesn't hurt.
Not at all.

00:13:40.381 --> 00:13:42.621
Is that why you wanted to meet?
Just to test that out?

00:13:43.021 --> 00:13:46.491
No. I want to ask when you're going
to court to finalize our divorce.

00:13:46.761 --> 00:13:47.761
Why do you ask?

00:13:47.761 --> 00:13:50.331
Why do you think? It'd be awkward
if we saw each other there.

00:13:50.531 --> 00:13:54.331
You could have just called me.
Why drag me out here? So annoying.

00:13:54.501 --> 00:13:55.901
Why are you so worked up...

00:13:58.401 --> 00:13:59.401
Don't.

00:14:00.871 --> 00:14:03.511
It works like a charm.
It really doesn't hurt.

00:14:03.811 --> 00:14:05.041
Seriously...

00:14:06.411 --> 00:14:08.911
Hey. Just text me
when you get a date, all right?

00:14:10.851 --> 00:14:11.851
It doesn't hurt.

00:14:12.411 --> 00:14:13.521
It's amazing.

00:14:22.461 --> 00:14:24.461
This is nice.

00:14:24.831 --> 00:14:27.261
The clothes are nice,
and you make them look even better.

00:14:27.531 --> 00:14:28.531
Perfect!

00:14:28.731 --> 00:14:30.701
Oh my, you're full
of compliments today.

00:14:31.431 --> 00:14:33.041
Are you that happy about us moving?

00:14:33.171 --> 00:14:36.571
No, I'm just happy
you're putting our family first.

00:14:37.971 --> 00:14:39.241
Right.

00:14:39.241 --> 00:14:42.711
Earlier, Dong Ik told me
not to move.

00:14:42.981 --> 00:14:44.011
Why all of a sudden?

00:14:44.051 --> 00:14:47.421
The show staff read the interview
we did for the local paper and...

00:14:47.421 --> 00:14:48.881
What was the show?

00:14:48.981 --> 00:14:53.391
- They want us for "Human Theater."
- "Human Theater?"

00:14:53.861 --> 00:14:56.761
- You and Dong Ik? Together?
- Yes.

00:14:57.091 --> 00:15:00.431
About a clinic and an oriental one
facing each other in the market.

00:15:00.701 --> 00:15:03.431
Fifty-some years of friendship.
A concept like that.

00:15:05.231 --> 00:15:08.141
He told you not to move
just to be on TV?

00:15:08.201 --> 00:15:12.211
Yes, he's a selfish jerk.
Either that or he's not all there.

00:15:12.271 --> 00:15:15.811
Did he even bother to ask
his wife's permission?

00:15:16.181 --> 00:15:18.951
I bet her biggest wish is
for us to move as soon as we can.

00:15:18.981 --> 00:15:20.481
Exactly.

00:15:20.721 --> 00:15:23.691
He's a total idiot.
An absolute moron.

00:15:25.091 --> 00:15:29.761
Honey, my wish is for that family
to move out as soon as possible.

00:15:30.091 --> 00:15:31.831
But this is "Human Theater"
we're talking about.

00:15:32.161 --> 00:15:33.761
This is my chance to be on TV.

00:15:34.901 --> 00:15:38.431
It's a shame, I know,
but there will be better chances.

00:15:38.531 --> 00:15:39.971
Until then,
you need to secure your spot...

00:15:39.971 --> 00:15:41.241
as the president
of the Merchants' Association.

00:15:41.341 --> 00:15:44.471
and just focus on your work.
All right?

00:15:50.311 --> 00:15:56.721
I wish I was on television
that would be really great

00:15:56.821 --> 00:15:58.321
Really, really great

00:16:13.741 --> 00:16:15.941
Running away again, Eun Bin?

00:16:15.941 --> 00:16:18.171
Yes, I'm not living here anymore!

00:16:18.241 --> 00:16:19.781
And I'm never coming back!

00:16:20.111 --> 00:16:21.281
Are you running off
to Woo Jae again?

00:16:21.611 --> 00:16:23.951
It's none of your business
where I go!

00:16:25.011 --> 00:16:26.221
You're not going anywhere.

00:16:26.581 --> 00:16:29.551
- Let go. I said let go!
- Oh my goodness.

00:16:30.621 --> 00:16:31.691
It's so heavy.

00:16:33.361 --> 00:16:36.131
- Hey! Get back here right now!
- What's wrong with you?

00:16:36.131 --> 00:16:38.461
- Honey! Father!
- What's with all the noise?

00:16:38.731 --> 00:16:42.671
- Now what's going on?
- Eun Bin's running away.

00:16:43.131 --> 00:16:46.141
I'm not living here anymore!
I'm going to live with Woo Jae!

00:16:46.371 --> 00:16:48.001
You little brat.
Are you going to keep this up?

00:16:48.641 --> 00:16:51.611
Grandfather, Dad.
Seriously, how could you do this?

00:16:51.711 --> 00:16:53.541
They've run that clinic
for 40 years.

00:16:53.541 --> 00:16:55.441
They've lived there all their lives.

00:16:55.581 --> 00:16:58.911
How can you just kick them out
overnight like that?

00:16:59.051 --> 00:17:01.721
Who said we're kicking them out?
Am I right, honey, Father?

00:17:02.921 --> 00:17:07.861
Blinded by jealousy of Dr. Han,
you framed and even attacked her.

00:17:07.961 --> 00:17:10.891
Then you used my aunt's tragedy
to manipulate Grandpa and Dad,

00:17:10.961 --> 00:17:14.831
and drove the Gongs out of Onjeong,
you evil witch!

00:17:15.001 --> 00:17:17.931
- You little brat, honestly!
- Yang Eun Bin!

00:17:18.101 --> 00:17:19.101
Get out.

00:17:19.171 --> 00:17:23.471
Fine, I'm leaving. I'd rather die.
I won't spend another day here!

00:17:23.941 --> 00:17:26.781
You little brat. You're grounded.

00:17:27.111 --> 00:17:29.981
Don't leave your room
until they move out. Got it?

00:17:30.111 --> 00:17:32.511
Go ahead.
I'll just starve myself to death.

00:17:32.981 --> 00:17:34.551
Install a CCTV camera
in her room now.

00:17:34.851 --> 00:17:37.591
Try it. I'll call the police!

00:17:37.921 --> 00:17:40.521
- You little brat! Come with me.
- What?

00:17:40.521 --> 00:17:42.961
- Get over here!
- Help! Police!

00:17:43.031 --> 00:17:45.231
- You think the police are your dad?
- You're hurting me.

00:17:45.291 --> 00:17:47.001
Then go live at the police station!
Get over here!

00:17:47.431 --> 00:17:49.331
Father, what are we going to do?

00:17:53.501 --> 00:17:54.501
What am I going to do?

00:17:58.541 --> 00:17:59.581
You little brat!

00:18:00.211 --> 00:18:02.181
How can you be so disrespectful?

00:18:02.311 --> 00:18:04.881
Get out!
I can't stand to look at you, Dad!

00:18:05.881 --> 00:18:08.551
- I won't make them move out.
- What? What did you say?

00:18:08.821 --> 00:18:09.821
You're unbelievable!

00:18:10.151 --> 00:18:13.061
Don't you dare leave this room.
Or you'll be sorry!

00:18:13.391 --> 00:18:17.531
- Really? You won't make them move?
- Yes, but you and Woo Jae are over.

00:18:17.591 --> 00:18:19.331
- Hey, come on...
- Hey, that's...

00:18:20.001 --> 00:18:22.031
We can talk about that later.

00:18:22.361 --> 00:18:24.771
For now, I won't make them move out,
so please just keep it down.

00:18:25.131 --> 00:18:27.901
- We're keeping this from stepmom?
- Yes.

00:18:28.301 --> 00:18:31.041
Hey!
Am I just talking to myself here?

00:18:31.871 --> 00:18:33.981
Give me your credit card.
It's confiscated.

00:18:34.341 --> 00:18:35.641
That’s low!

00:18:35.641 --> 00:18:37.911
- Raise my credit card limit.
- What did you just say?

00:18:40.081 --> 00:18:41.251
Don't push your luck, kid!

00:18:41.621 --> 00:18:42.621
Or I'm telling her.

00:18:44.291 --> 00:18:47.121
- This is so unfair!
- Are you going to answer me or not?

00:18:47.391 --> 00:18:49.761
Honey, please, that's enough now.
Okay?

00:18:50.161 --> 00:18:53.761
Fine. I get it. I won't run away.

00:18:53.901 --> 00:18:56.931
You mean it? And if you ever do that
in front of your stepmom again...

00:18:57.001 --> 00:19:01.371
I get it! So I must listen to her
from now on, right?

00:19:02.301 --> 00:19:03.941
Oh, dear.

00:19:14.451 --> 00:19:15.451
She's gone.

00:19:15.821 --> 00:19:18.591
How will you stop their move?
Do you even have a plan?

00:19:18.851 --> 00:19:20.761
What plan could I possibly have?
I've got nothing.

00:19:21.591 --> 00:19:23.061
What am I going to do about this?

00:19:23.161 --> 00:19:26.231
Dad, you should start
at the police substation.

00:19:26.761 --> 00:19:29.101
The police substation? Why there?

00:19:30.331 --> 00:19:31.971
(Onjeong Police Substation)

00:19:32.031 --> 00:19:34.771
Come on, Nurse Oh,
just eat with us, please?

00:19:34.841 --> 00:19:36.541
No, thank you. I'll pass.

00:19:37.111 --> 00:19:40.381
Anyway, why is the clinic closed
this afternoon?

00:19:41.741 --> 00:19:44.651
Director Gong
went for a job interview today.

00:19:44.751 --> 00:19:47.021
But you're staying, right?

00:19:47.351 --> 00:19:48.451
Yes, I guess.

00:19:49.121 --> 00:19:50.751
I was planning
to go with him, but...

00:19:52.251 --> 00:19:54.561
I'm glad you're not going.

00:19:59.531 --> 00:20:03.271
No, I didn't mean anything by it.

00:20:03.501 --> 00:20:06.441
Don't get a crush on me.
I have high standards.

00:20:06.571 --> 00:20:09.071
How can you turn me down
when I haven't even said anything?

00:20:09.201 --> 00:20:10.371
Anyway...

00:20:10.811 --> 00:20:13.141
I'm so excited just thinking about
moving into that house.

00:20:13.841 --> 00:20:14.881
So excited.

00:20:16.281 --> 00:20:17.911
- It's a really nice house.
- Yes, it is.

00:20:17.911 --> 00:20:20.521
Oh my, you're having lunch.

00:20:24.921 --> 00:20:28.791
Here, I brought an herbal supplement
to boost your energy.

00:20:29.561 --> 00:20:32.591
And you can put it right
on your shoulders.

00:20:32.661 --> 00:20:34.931
It feels great. It's a heat pack.

00:20:35.831 --> 00:20:39.331
You're on patrol all day,
holding those walkie-talkies...

00:20:39.401 --> 00:20:41.071
and dealing with difficult complaints
from citizens.

00:20:41.341 --> 00:20:42.941
It must be so exhausting for you.

00:20:43.511 --> 00:20:45.111
We appreciate the gesture,

00:20:45.371 --> 00:20:48.911
- but we can't accept gifts.
- Is that right?

00:20:49.651 --> 00:20:52.011
This is embarrassing.

00:20:52.921 --> 00:20:55.081
So, what brings you here today,
Director Yang?

00:20:55.751 --> 00:20:57.121
Well...

00:20:58.551 --> 00:21:01.121
You know the contract you signed
for that house?

00:21:01.761 --> 00:21:05.091
Chief, I was hoping
you might cancel it.

00:21:05.191 --> 00:21:06.401
- What?
- Oh my.

00:21:06.461 --> 00:21:09.161
I'll cover
any and all financial losses.

00:21:09.831 --> 00:21:10.931
But didn't you want...

00:21:11.331 --> 00:21:14.571
Director Gong's family
to move out of Onjeong?

00:21:14.641 --> 00:21:16.201
Not at all.

00:21:16.741 --> 00:21:19.341
It's just that so many bad things
have been happening,

00:21:19.581 --> 00:21:22.141
my intention was
to escape all the misfortune.

00:21:22.241 --> 00:21:26.111
But it'll be hard for me
to find another place that nice.

00:21:26.211 --> 00:21:28.121
You're familiar
with feng shui, right?

00:21:28.421 --> 00:21:32.651
I believe the energy and lifeblood
of a place are very important.

00:21:32.891 --> 00:21:35.421
When a house has been cared for
by one family for decades,

00:21:35.891 --> 00:21:37.031
the very land itself...

00:21:37.091 --> 00:21:41.701
becomes deeply imbued
with their spiritual essence, right?

00:21:42.261 --> 00:21:44.101
Here, let me take your pulse.

00:21:44.831 --> 00:21:46.771
Gosh, a place like that...

00:21:46.771 --> 00:21:48.201
Just trust me on this.

00:21:48.341 --> 00:21:51.471
It won't easily accept a new owner.

00:21:53.141 --> 00:21:56.651
See? Your pulse is weak.
You must be exhausted.

00:21:56.751 --> 00:21:57.851
You need to move
into a newly built place.

00:21:58.281 --> 00:22:00.481
- Should I get an apartment?
- Hey, that's a great idea.

00:22:03.251 --> 00:22:05.021
- All right, take care now.
- You too.

00:22:11.791 --> 00:22:13.231
Oh, yes, ma'am.

00:22:13.661 --> 00:22:18.501
Ma'am, we have a problem.
This is so awkward.

00:22:18.801 --> 00:22:21.701
The Chief says he wants to cancel
the contract on the house.

00:22:22.241 --> 00:22:26.881
What? Cancel the contract?
Why all of a sudden?

00:22:27.481 --> 00:22:31.481
Was there something
he didn't like about our house?

00:22:31.781 --> 00:22:36.721
Oh, no, it's not that. Apparently,
his mother-in-law is against it.

00:22:37.221 --> 00:22:42.121
I see. I understand
how things are with the elders.

00:22:42.561 --> 00:22:45.991
He said he's willing to forfeit
the deposit, as per the agreement.

00:22:46.131 --> 00:22:49.231
That's not necessary.
It's not like we're strangers.

00:22:49.301 --> 00:22:51.231
I'll return his deposit.

00:22:52.171 --> 00:22:54.341
Yes, I understand.

00:22:58.441 --> 00:22:59.511
Hey, Jin Ah...

00:23:12.821 --> 00:23:14.691
What is it? Nurse Oh,
why are you blocking my way?

00:23:14.761 --> 00:23:17.631
You convinced the Chief
to cancel his contract, didn't you?

00:23:18.591 --> 00:23:20.931
No, I didn't.

00:23:21.761 --> 00:23:23.931
Don't worry. I'm on your side.

00:23:24.401 --> 00:23:25.401
You are?

00:23:30.011 --> 00:23:34.281
So, what's the next plan?
Because I can offer you some intel.

00:23:36.311 --> 00:23:37.951
The skies must be on my side.

00:23:38.281 --> 00:23:40.681
To have reinforcements popping up
out of nowhere like this.

00:23:42.581 --> 00:23:43.591
Here, have some.

00:23:46.291 --> 00:23:48.991
Using the experience I've gained
working in community healthcare,

00:23:49.061 --> 00:23:52.091
I want to treat every patient
at this hospital...

00:23:52.191 --> 00:23:55.001
with a true sense of responsibility.

00:23:55.301 --> 00:23:58.201
I don't want to just
treat the illness,

00:23:58.301 --> 00:23:59.871
but the person's body and mind...

00:23:59.941 --> 00:24:04.041
But we have
a high patient volume here,

00:24:04.441 --> 00:24:08.141
we prioritize efficiency and speed
over one person's philosophy.

00:24:08.211 --> 00:24:09.481
Of course.

00:24:10.351 --> 00:24:13.821
If I join, I'll naturally follow
your principles, Director.

00:24:14.121 --> 00:24:16.891
It says here you've been running...

00:24:17.021 --> 00:24:20.261
a third-generation clinic
in one area.

00:24:20.261 --> 00:24:21.661
Yes.

00:24:21.991 --> 00:24:25.131
I grew old right
alongside my patients.

00:24:25.191 --> 00:24:27.061
But people like you often...

00:24:27.131 --> 00:24:30.801
have a difficult time adjusting
to the organizational structure.

00:24:31.231 --> 00:24:35.301
Well, I'd have to adapt.
I can do it.

00:24:50.751 --> 00:24:54.661
Hello, Dr. Jo, I was actually
just about to call you.

00:24:56.091 --> 00:24:59.131
What? A different hospital?

00:25:00.101 --> 00:25:01.801
Wait, why all of a sudden?

00:25:05.201 --> 00:25:06.401
The distance?

00:25:07.401 --> 00:25:10.111
Yes, that's true. It is a bit far.

00:25:11.271 --> 00:25:13.341
All right, I understand.

00:25:14.411 --> 00:25:16.981
Yes, I'll start looking again.

00:25:18.051 --> 00:25:19.051
Okay.

00:25:29.261 --> 00:25:31.061
Well, well, Dr. Jo.

00:25:31.491 --> 00:25:33.561
Thank you so much
for turning it down.

00:25:34.101 --> 00:25:36.931
Yes, that's right.
Our Director Gong is truly...

00:25:37.001 --> 00:25:40.071
indispensable to the people
at the market.

00:25:40.841 --> 00:25:44.211
Gosh, at your age, coming
all this way here from Icheon...

00:25:44.911 --> 00:25:47.911
How could you possibly manage
a one to two-hour commute?

00:25:48.041 --> 00:25:49.081
Right.

00:25:49.141 --> 00:25:53.221
As promised, I'll surely find you
a position that's a better fit.

00:25:53.321 --> 00:25:56.651
Okay, thank you. Take care.

00:25:59.721 --> 00:26:02.361
Do you really think this is okay?

00:26:03.061 --> 00:26:04.491
Of course.

00:26:04.661 --> 00:26:08.601
I'm sure this is
what Director Gong would want.

00:26:15.671 --> 00:26:16.711
I'm back.

00:26:19.571 --> 00:26:21.681
How did the interview go?

00:26:22.311 --> 00:26:25.311
It was not bad.
I have a few more interviews.

00:26:27.081 --> 00:26:29.251
The real estate agent called,

00:26:30.021 --> 00:26:34.261
and the Chief canceled the contract
on our house.

00:26:34.391 --> 00:26:35.461
All of a sudden?

00:26:35.791 --> 00:26:37.531
But he already sent the deposit.

00:26:37.631 --> 00:26:40.661
I'm sure he had his reasons.

00:26:41.631 --> 00:26:43.131
Right, but still...

00:26:45.831 --> 00:26:46.901
(Pharmacy)

00:26:51.111 --> 00:26:53.541
What is this uneasy feeling?

00:26:54.241 --> 00:26:57.281
This is so strange.
Why is everyone suddenly canceling?

00:27:00.651 --> 00:27:02.251
Don't tell me...

00:27:03.951 --> 00:27:05.291
That's right.

00:27:05.521 --> 00:27:08.721
I'm the one who convinced
the Chief and Dr. Jo.

00:27:09.261 --> 00:27:10.861
You've got to be kidding me!

00:27:11.331 --> 00:27:13.701
Are you out of your mind?
Have you lost it?

00:27:14.361 --> 00:27:15.531
Unbelievable.

00:27:15.601 --> 00:27:17.071
Jeong Han.

00:27:17.071 --> 00:27:18.601
Hey, Mr. "Fair" Jeong Han!

00:27:18.601 --> 00:27:20.541
Your name means "fair," doesn't it?
Come on, just this once.

00:27:20.541 --> 00:27:22.341
Just think it over one more time.

00:27:22.641 --> 00:27:25.171
You're forcing yourself to leave
when you don't want to.

00:27:25.241 --> 00:27:28.811
You're right. It was a very hard decision
for me to make!

00:27:28.911 --> 00:27:31.481
You're asking me to go back on it
for your own selfish reasons?

00:27:31.481 --> 00:27:33.521
You even pulled a bizarre stunt
like this!

00:27:33.551 --> 00:27:38.491
Hey, selfish reasons? No.
This is to help Onjeong Market.

00:27:38.551 --> 00:27:40.121
That's ridiculous!

00:27:40.221 --> 00:27:43.761
No, I'm serious.
What about your patients?

00:27:43.831 --> 00:27:47.431
You're like family to them.

00:27:47.501 --> 00:27:49.631
Why? Because they trust you.

00:27:50.971 --> 00:27:53.671
You don't just treat
their illnesses,

00:27:53.741 --> 00:27:56.071
you see what's in their hearts.

00:27:56.671 --> 00:27:59.841
Hey, think about it.
The void you'll leave behind.

00:27:59.911 --> 00:28:03.311
No other doctor could ever fill it.
Don't you think?

00:28:03.311 --> 00:28:06.821
You'll really say anything
to get elected to city council?

00:28:07.081 --> 00:28:10.791
Remember why I decided to move,
you idiot.

00:28:10.921 --> 00:28:13.291
What about Dae Han and Dong Suk?

00:28:13.361 --> 00:28:16.421
Don't worry.
I'll figure it out, too. Okay?

00:28:16.491 --> 00:28:19.761
What could you possibly do?
The pharmacy's already been leased!

00:28:19.761 --> 00:28:24.001
Exactly.
Do you know who leased the pharmacy?

00:28:24.401 --> 00:28:26.231
How should I know, you idiot!

00:28:27.141 --> 00:28:28.141
Hey...

00:28:30.241 --> 00:28:31.941
Then I'll find out myself.

00:28:33.141 --> 00:28:34.241
I will.

00:28:36.281 --> 00:28:39.011
Come on. I said it's confidential,
Director Yang.

00:28:39.051 --> 00:28:41.851
Okay. Then a hint!
Just give me a little hint.

00:28:42.121 --> 00:28:43.251
Please. I'm begging you.

00:28:43.321 --> 00:28:45.821
If that deal falls through,
I don't get my commission.

00:28:45.891 --> 00:28:48.321
Come on. Why are you being
like this?

00:28:48.391 --> 00:28:51.191
But I already paid your commission
for the house cancellation, right?

00:28:51.331 --> 00:28:55.431
Not the pharmacy.
They told me not to say a word.

00:28:55.501 --> 00:28:59.531
So who is it?
Come on, just tell me...

00:29:03.141 --> 00:29:04.771
On second thought,

00:29:06.071 --> 00:29:07.141
you don't have to.

00:29:09.981 --> 00:29:12.181
Why? I told you
I was just passing by.

00:29:12.481 --> 00:29:16.181
Why would you just be
passing by a real estate office?

00:29:17.691 --> 00:29:20.291
So what?
What are you accusing me of?

00:29:20.391 --> 00:29:23.591
I'm not accusing you.
I'm just curious.

00:29:23.691 --> 00:29:25.561
Why you helped them.

00:29:25.831 --> 00:29:29.101
They have to move because of us.
You expect me not to help?

00:29:29.201 --> 00:29:32.671
Come on.
Then we shouldn't make them move.

00:29:34.001 --> 00:29:35.001
What are you talking about?

00:29:35.071 --> 00:29:38.811
The rent and deposit money you'd pay
until the new pharmacy moved in.

00:29:39.171 --> 00:29:40.811
Let's use it for something else.

00:29:44.651 --> 00:29:47.381
So that's why it got sold so fast.

00:29:47.751 --> 00:29:50.621
Once people know we're moving,
the house will be sold again soon.

00:29:51.291 --> 00:29:54.421
You're right.
After I let my patients know,

00:29:54.561 --> 00:29:56.661
I'm going to list it
with other agencies too.

00:30:02.701 --> 00:30:03.801
Yes, hello?

00:30:06.701 --> 00:30:07.701
What?

00:30:08.701 --> 00:30:11.571
What do you mean
the pharmacy contract was canceled?

00:30:13.641 --> 00:30:16.781
Okay, I understand.

00:30:18.751 --> 00:30:20.351
What?
The pharmacy deal was canceled?

00:30:20.451 --> 00:30:23.951
Seriously,
why are so many people so flaky?

00:30:24.021 --> 00:30:25.221
This is so frustrating.

00:30:27.121 --> 00:30:30.091
I'm sorry. It's something from work.

00:30:30.991 --> 00:30:33.331
What can you do?

00:30:33.601 --> 00:30:36.201
Besides, Mom, you had a bad feeling
about it anyway, didn't you?

00:30:36.931 --> 00:30:37.931
That's true.

00:30:38.531 --> 00:30:41.801
He offered to pay the rent
until a new pharmacy moved in,

00:30:42.741 --> 00:30:44.271
but that was a huge burden for me.

00:30:53.521 --> 00:30:55.651
Wait a minute.
Don't tell me Dong Ik...

00:31:01.061 --> 00:31:04.391
See? I do what I set out to do.
Don't worry about your brother.

00:31:04.531 --> 00:31:05.591
Just leave it all to me.

00:31:05.931 --> 00:31:06.931
Darn it...

00:31:07.801 --> 00:31:09.231
Darn him, why would he...

00:31:09.831 --> 00:31:12.601
Seriously,
what does he think he's doing?

00:31:12.931 --> 00:31:13.941
Darn it.

00:31:14.941 --> 00:31:15.941
Me?

00:31:16.441 --> 00:31:18.571
You're going to set me up
with my own store, Dad?

00:31:18.671 --> 00:31:21.441
That's right.
Just pick whatever shop you want.

00:31:21.981 --> 00:31:25.411
Oh my goodness, Father.
How could you be so thoughtful?

00:31:25.551 --> 00:31:27.421
That was my idea.

00:31:27.681 --> 00:31:28.681
Really?

00:31:29.021 --> 00:31:30.951
Thank you, honey.

00:31:30.951 --> 00:31:33.821
This is so great for you, Dong Suk.
Congratulations.

00:31:34.121 --> 00:31:36.121
I'm so touched.

00:31:36.591 --> 00:31:39.331
And here I thought
I was living completely unloved.

00:31:39.891 --> 00:31:41.561
Mom, does that mean you're going
to be a business owner?

00:31:42.561 --> 00:31:45.001
You're so lucky, Auntie,
getting to be a boss.

00:31:45.001 --> 00:31:46.701
Now you're the CEO Yang Dong Suk.

00:31:46.771 --> 00:31:48.771
I know, right?
What kind of shop should I open?

00:31:48.841 --> 00:31:50.571
Gosh, I have so much to think about.

00:31:50.641 --> 00:31:54.311
- Let's check properties, Dong Suk.
- Okay.

00:32:08.791 --> 00:32:11.531
Father, thank you for your help.

00:32:12.091 --> 00:32:13.231
Should we do this
without telling Se Ri?

00:32:13.631 --> 00:32:15.831
Are you sure you can do this
without telling Se Ri?

00:32:16.431 --> 00:32:20.971
I'll handle it with her later.
First, I must convince their family.

00:32:21.301 --> 00:32:22.671
When you tell Se Ri,

00:32:22.941 --> 00:32:24.971
leave me out of it.
I didn't know anything, you hear?

00:32:25.441 --> 00:32:28.781
Grandpa, that's so cowardly.
We're already in the same boat.

00:32:28.841 --> 00:32:29.881
You little!

00:32:30.251 --> 00:32:33.011
You're absolutely forbidden to see
that boy from the clinic. Got it?

00:32:33.211 --> 00:32:37.351
Don't worry. I'll make sure
they never get involved again.

00:32:39.491 --> 00:32:41.621
- Don't even think about it.
- Unbelievable.

00:32:46.661 --> 00:32:47.861
Where is he?

00:32:52.331 --> 00:32:54.971
Hey, what did you do now
with the pharmacy deal?

00:32:55.371 --> 00:32:56.401
The thing is...

00:32:56.841 --> 00:32:58.511
Turns out, the one who signed
the lease was my father.

00:32:58.871 --> 00:33:02.241
- What?
- It seems he wanted to help you.

00:33:02.511 --> 00:33:05.811
He may act like you're his enemies,
but deep down, he feels differently.

00:33:06.851 --> 00:33:10.951
When I said to use the money for
Dong Suk's store, he agreed at once.

00:33:11.791 --> 00:33:14.321
- Dong Suk is opening her own store?
- Yes.

00:33:14.661 --> 00:33:18.131
Dong Suk is quitting the clinic,
so she won't run into Dae Han.

00:33:18.331 --> 00:33:20.301
Now everything that bothered you
is resolved, right?

00:33:22.901 --> 00:33:25.671
Okay, but why did you drag me out
in the middle of the night?

00:33:26.331 --> 00:33:27.971
The thing is, Jeong Han...

00:33:28.671 --> 00:33:29.671
Tomorrow...

00:33:29.941 --> 00:33:31.741
The Human Theater producer
is coming to see us.

00:33:32.011 --> 00:33:34.841
What? Did you set up a meeting
without asking me?

00:33:35.081 --> 00:33:36.941
No, it's not that I scheduled it.

00:33:37.581 --> 00:33:38.951
They just said
the producer is coming.

00:33:39.581 --> 00:33:42.421
- Forget it! Meet them yourself.
- Come on, don't be like that.

00:33:43.721 --> 00:33:44.721
Here.

00:33:45.791 --> 00:33:46.791
Take this.

00:33:48.261 --> 00:33:49.361
What's this?

00:33:49.891 --> 00:33:50.961
This is...

00:33:51.531 --> 00:33:54.101
Let's call it a pledge
of my devotion to you.

00:33:54.731 --> 00:33:55.961
That's disgusting! Seriously.

00:33:56.531 --> 00:33:58.771
- What kind of pledge?
- Just...

00:33:59.201 --> 00:34:00.641
- Just read it.
- Gosh.

00:34:00.901 --> 00:34:04.871
I'll text you the time and place
for our meeting. Okay? Got it?

00:34:05.541 --> 00:34:09.841
- Sleep tight, my friend.
- Gosh.

00:34:09.911 --> 00:34:12.651
Hey, we're definitely meeting
tomorrow, you hear me?

00:34:13.551 --> 00:34:14.921
Chairman, I'll be
on my way then. Yes.

00:34:15.821 --> 00:34:16.821
That guy.

00:34:17.491 --> 00:34:19.351
What's gotten into him lately?
Seriously, that guy.

00:34:19.821 --> 00:34:20.821
Gosh.

00:34:29.231 --> 00:34:30.901
Seriously.

00:34:37.041 --> 00:34:39.271
What's this? A pledge?

00:34:39.841 --> 00:34:43.881
This certifies that Gong Jeong Han
has retracted his decision to move,

00:34:44.251 --> 00:34:48.221
and in gratitude for agreeing
to appear on "Human Theater,"

00:34:48.651 --> 00:34:52.651
Yang Dong Ik hereby pledges
his loyalty to Gong Jeong Han.

00:34:53.821 --> 00:34:55.721
Henceforth, Yang Dong Ik...

00:34:56.291 --> 00:34:59.831
shall obey all his orders
without question,

00:35:00.431 --> 00:35:05.001
and when summoned by Gong Jeong Han,
regardless of time or place,

00:35:05.071 --> 00:35:06.171
he shall report immediately...

00:35:06.631 --> 00:35:08.941
and perform all duties
entrusted to him...

00:35:09.201 --> 00:35:12.441
with his entire being.
He so pledges.

00:35:12.711 --> 00:35:14.781
Hey, do we really
have to go this far?

00:35:14.841 --> 00:35:18.011
We have to. It's the only way
he'll meet the producer tomorrow.

00:35:18.081 --> 00:35:19.711
Write it like you mean it! Hurry!

00:35:20.381 --> 00:35:22.021
I, Yang Dong Ik, henceforth...

00:35:22.551 --> 00:35:24.351
I, Yang Dong Ik, henceforth...

00:35:24.891 --> 00:35:28.621
shall never again criticize
Gong Jeong Han in word or deed,

00:35:28.761 --> 00:35:31.031
and should I break
any of these promises...

00:35:31.461 --> 00:35:33.931
Any punishment that Gong Jeong Han
deems fit...

00:35:34.101 --> 00:35:37.371
I shall accept willingly.
I so solemnly swear.

00:35:38.601 --> 00:35:42.541
What the heck?
He basically wrote a slave contract.

00:35:43.071 --> 00:35:45.511
What is that punk
trying to pull this time?

00:35:56.751 --> 00:35:58.721
In the place
where you promised to come,

00:36:00.251 --> 00:36:02.961
as I wait for you,
having come early,

00:36:04.631 --> 00:36:06.591
every approaching footstep...

00:36:07.901 --> 00:36:09.631
pounds in my heart.

00:36:13.401 --> 00:36:15.301
Even a single rustling leaf...

00:36:16.741 --> 00:36:17.971
sounds like you.

00:36:22.111 --> 00:36:25.911
Next time, be sure to get a refill
before your medication runs out.

00:36:26.111 --> 00:36:29.251
- Okay, thank you.
- Yes, of course. Take care.

00:36:29.521 --> 00:36:31.251
- This way, please.
- Okay.

00:36:37.331 --> 00:36:39.631
Anyone who's ever truly waited
knows.

00:36:40.601 --> 00:36:42.961
In this world, is there anything...

00:36:43.901 --> 00:36:45.771
more agonizing than waiting?

00:36:50.541 --> 00:36:52.141
In the place
where you promised to come,

00:36:53.641 --> 00:36:55.241
here where I have come early,

00:36:58.881 --> 00:37:01.521
every person approaching was you,

00:37:02.951 --> 00:37:04.121
then you again,

00:37:05.921 --> 00:37:07.521
and then it was almost you.

00:37:18.631 --> 00:37:22.471
- Jeong Han! Hey, thanks for coming!
- You're unbelievable! Seriously!

00:37:22.541 --> 00:37:26.171
- Man, thank you so much!
- Get off me!

00:37:27.741 --> 00:37:29.281
Nothing's been decided yet.

00:37:30.411 --> 00:37:31.951
- Let's go.
- What?

00:37:33.181 --> 00:37:36.451
Our production team was impressed
with the article about you two.

00:37:36.951 --> 00:37:38.921
The friendship you've built
since you were children,

00:37:39.351 --> 00:37:41.461
the contrast between being a doctor
and a Korean medicine doctor,

00:37:41.891 --> 00:37:44.561
and your role as partners
leading the market...

00:37:44.861 --> 00:37:46.431
It all makes for a wonderful
narrative.

00:37:48.001 --> 00:37:49.501
You're far too kind.

00:37:50.061 --> 00:37:54.371
Our Onjeong Market is a very warm
and welcoming place,

00:37:54.601 --> 00:37:57.101
so we'd like to use this chance
to promote it.

00:37:57.941 --> 00:38:00.911
Excuse me, but for the sake of
making the show more entertaining,

00:38:00.981 --> 00:38:05.151
I hear editing can be sensational
or that facts can be distorted.

00:38:05.281 --> 00:38:07.981
That's something I'm a little
concerned about.

00:38:08.351 --> 00:38:12.591
If you're worried, we can put that
in the contract for you.

00:38:14.221 --> 00:38:15.221
The thing is,

00:38:15.561 --> 00:38:17.731
our daily lives are just...

00:38:17.791 --> 00:38:21.001
pretty ordinary and predictable.

00:38:21.331 --> 00:38:24.531
I doubt they will be as entertaining
as you might expect.

00:38:24.971 --> 00:38:28.941
What we're looking for is
the extraordinary in the ordinary.

00:38:30.201 --> 00:38:34.441
If ratings are high, it's a win-win
for the network and for us, right?

00:38:34.911 --> 00:38:36.611
If you just set up the scenarios,

00:38:36.911 --> 00:38:40.721
we're ready and willing to do
whatever you tell us. Yes.

00:38:40.951 --> 00:38:44.821
Then do you have any special talents
you want to show off?

00:38:45.091 --> 00:38:48.491
I'm actually pretty good
at Chinese. Yes.

00:38:55.461 --> 00:38:58.801
Oh my.
Welcome to our Onjeong Market.

00:38:58.871 --> 00:39:01.001
- We sincerely welcome you.
- Don't. Just don't.

00:39:01.071 --> 00:39:03.971
This place offers
a wide variety of food...

00:39:04.041 --> 00:39:08.641
and is full of warm,
generous people.

00:39:09.681 --> 00:39:12.311
You pledged you wouldn't do that
if I told you to. Unbelievable.

00:39:13.281 --> 00:39:16.551
Right. About that pledge,
I just meant...

00:39:17.451 --> 00:39:19.421
I love this dynamic.

00:39:20.351 --> 00:39:21.521
They're like Tom and Jerry.

00:39:22.521 --> 00:39:24.091
That's basically us.

00:39:24.391 --> 00:39:27.531
- Tom and Jerry. I'm Jerry.
- Right.

00:39:31.031 --> 00:39:32.701
- Hey, say goodbye.
- Goodbye.

00:39:36.601 --> 00:39:37.911
Hey, what's there to think about?

00:39:39.371 --> 00:39:40.371
Gosh, but you...

00:39:40.911 --> 00:39:43.111
Did you even get your wife's
permission for this?

00:39:43.741 --> 00:39:45.751
Look, not to brag,

00:39:46.781 --> 00:39:49.651
but I’m basically Se Ri's
whole world. What I say goes.

00:39:51.191 --> 00:39:53.321
But it's going to be a lot tougher
for you, right?

00:39:56.221 --> 00:39:58.861
Seong Mi even did a commercial
to save up for our moving costs.

00:39:58.931 --> 00:40:01.001
So if I suddenly tell her
we're not moving anymore,

00:40:01.101 --> 00:40:03.061
man, that's grounds for divorce.

00:40:03.701 --> 00:40:06.371
Hey, then just use me as an excuse.
Blame it all on me.

00:40:07.301 --> 00:40:10.471
Gosh, do you really want to be on TV
that badly?

00:40:10.541 --> 00:40:13.871
I want to make
Korean herbal medicine global...

00:40:14.211 --> 00:40:17.881
and show the whole world
how great it is.

00:40:18.181 --> 00:40:21.651
- Give me a break.
- And...

00:40:21.921 --> 00:40:23.951
lots of people will watch
"Human Theater," right?

00:40:25.021 --> 00:40:26.121
So my mom...

00:40:27.121 --> 00:40:28.291
and my kids' mom...

00:40:29.221 --> 00:40:30.521
can see me
wherever they are, won't they?

00:40:35.101 --> 00:40:38.101
You have Seong Mi to show off
your family on TV, but I don't.

00:40:40.031 --> 00:40:41.801
I want to proudly show them
how I'm doing.

00:40:42.901 --> 00:40:46.011
How well the children they abandoned
are doing,

00:40:46.971 --> 00:40:48.581
how well my kids have grown up...

00:40:49.641 --> 00:40:51.951
I just want to proudly show them
what they're missing.

00:40:58.251 --> 00:41:00.421
Fine. By the weekend...

00:41:01.091 --> 00:41:02.791
I'll talk to Seong Mi. Gosh.

00:41:04.261 --> 00:41:05.261
Hey.

00:41:05.861 --> 00:41:06.861
Thank you. I mean it.

00:41:09.631 --> 00:41:11.701
I can see the divorce papers now.
Seriously.

00:41:15.701 --> 00:41:20.271
This restaurant is on a main street.
The owner's retiring and selling it.

00:41:20.671 --> 00:41:23.141
Business isn't exactly booming,

00:41:23.411 --> 00:41:26.511
but it's an urgent sale and cheap.
You should go take a look.

00:41:42.061 --> 00:41:43.101
What can I get you?

00:41:46.571 --> 00:41:49.671
- About the restaurant...
- We only have the braised dish now.

00:41:51.371 --> 00:41:52.641
I'll have one of those.

00:41:59.681 --> 00:42:01.821
I guess this place mostly caters
to drinkers.

00:42:11.091 --> 00:42:14.161
- Darn it!
- Oh my gosh, are you okay, ma'am?

00:42:14.231 --> 00:42:17.401
What the heck!
Watch where you're going!

00:42:17.731 --> 00:42:20.941
- I'm so sorry.
- Gosh, it's all over me!

00:42:21.401 --> 00:42:23.801
Come on,
is this how you treat a regular?

00:42:24.511 --> 00:42:27.241
- You're paying for my dry cleaning.
- What?

00:42:27.411 --> 00:42:31.711
- Or don't charge for the drinks.
- Excuse me, sir.

00:42:32.151 --> 00:42:35.381
You stumbled and bumped into her.
You should be apologizing,

00:42:35.721 --> 00:42:37.591
not demanding she pay for cleaning
and give you free drinks.

00:42:37.721 --> 00:42:41.121
Hey, who do you think you are,
meddling in others' business?

00:42:41.361 --> 00:42:43.821
- Oh, dear.
- Here, get up and have a seat.

00:42:44.391 --> 00:42:46.261
Good grief. Look,

00:42:46.731 --> 00:42:48.801
you've had enough to drink.
Please leave.

00:42:49.601 --> 00:42:51.171
Don't worry about the bill.

00:42:51.571 --> 00:42:56.341
Ma'am, why not make him pay?
This is why jerks like him return.

00:42:56.801 --> 00:42:59.571
Hey!
Think you can say whatever you want?

00:42:59.941 --> 00:43:02.611
Who do you think you're talking to?

00:43:02.611 --> 00:43:03.641
What?

00:43:05.111 --> 00:43:08.221
- Are you talking down to me?
- Yes, I am. What about it?

00:43:09.321 --> 00:43:13.391
It's unbelievable
how people like you still exist.

00:43:13.691 --> 00:43:18.131
- You did it on purpose to not pay.
- What are you talking about?

00:43:18.461 --> 00:43:21.301
Look at your eyes darting around,
I knew it.

00:43:21.861 --> 00:43:24.701
Hey, someone call the police!
We've got a dine and dasher here!

00:43:24.771 --> 00:43:28.171
Hey! Darn it. Fine, I'll pay.
I'll pay, all right?

00:43:28.341 --> 00:43:31.271
There, I'll pay. Happy now? Gosh.

00:43:33.471 --> 00:43:37.281
There. Happy now?
Just my rotten luck.

00:43:37.511 --> 00:43:38.881
Darn it.

00:43:40.281 --> 00:43:41.321
Hey!

00:43:44.951 --> 00:43:45.951
Pick it up.

00:43:46.251 --> 00:43:50.821
- Pick it up now and hand it to her.
- For crying out loud!

00:43:50.991 --> 00:43:55.501
Enough! You witch!
If you keep acting so nasty,

00:43:55.661 --> 00:43:58.871
your husband's going to leave you.
You hear me?

00:43:59.871 --> 00:44:02.641
- What?
- What? Did he already leave you?

00:44:02.941 --> 00:44:06.141
Your shifty eyes give it all away.
I knew it.

00:44:06.311 --> 00:44:10.381
Says you.
Have you even held a woman's hand?

00:44:10.711 --> 00:44:11.711
What?

00:44:12.011 --> 00:44:14.251
This witch...
You've got a death wish?

00:44:15.651 --> 00:44:20.551
- Hit me! Why won't you hit me?
- I can't, I can't. That hurts!

00:44:21.021 --> 00:44:23.221
How is your grip so strong? Darn it.

00:44:23.821 --> 00:44:28.401
- What are you? Some kind of thug?
- No, sir, I'm a physical therapist.

00:44:28.731 --> 00:44:32.871
- I'm strong from working on bodies.
- Gosh!

00:44:32.931 --> 00:44:37.541
Your hamstrings are really tight.
Let me give you a little massage.

00:44:38.271 --> 00:44:39.411
I was wrong.

00:44:39.741 --> 00:44:43.411
- I said I was wrong!
- I'll let you go,

00:44:43.941 --> 00:44:46.411
but first, give them a real apology.
If you don't...

00:44:46.551 --> 00:44:49.481
Oh my!

00:44:51.221 --> 00:44:55.961
- Now for the psoas muscle.
- Okay, I'll do it!

00:44:56.021 --> 00:44:57.021
I can't hear you.

00:44:57.191 --> 00:44:58.761
I said I'll do it!

00:45:03.861 --> 00:45:05.131
You haven't changed a bit
since we were kids.

00:45:05.801 --> 00:45:07.841
You've always had more guts
than sense.

00:45:08.901 --> 00:45:10.201
I just don't get you.

00:45:17.381 --> 00:45:18.381
Are you okay?

00:45:20.111 --> 00:45:21.121
I mean...

00:45:22.321 --> 00:45:23.881
It's finally sinking in.

00:45:24.851 --> 00:45:25.851
What is?

00:45:28.021 --> 00:45:29.061
That I don't have...

00:45:30.321 --> 00:45:31.861
a husband anymore.

00:45:36.061 --> 00:45:37.061
Hey.

00:45:37.801 --> 00:45:39.301
I'm in the exact same boat,
you know.

00:45:39.871 --> 00:45:41.001
Don't you start.

00:45:41.741 --> 00:45:43.341
If you cry,
I'm going to start bawling too.

00:45:47.911 --> 00:45:49.141
Come on, stop.

00:45:50.641 --> 00:45:52.011
If you stop,
I'll buy you your favorite meat.

00:45:53.911 --> 00:45:54.921
The boneless short ribs.

00:46:15.071 --> 00:46:17.841
Clear all my counseling appointments
for the rest of the year.

00:46:18.041 --> 00:46:20.911
Yes, Doctor.
Is this for your modeling schedule?

00:46:20.971 --> 00:46:21.981
Yes.

00:46:23.741 --> 00:46:27.981
- Oh, honey. What's up?
- Seong Mi, let's date this weekend.

00:46:28.821 --> 00:46:30.321
A date? What's the occasion?

00:46:32.551 --> 00:46:34.321
You know that restaurant you love?

00:46:34.791 --> 00:46:35.791
Porto Veli?

00:46:36.861 --> 00:46:38.561
You got us a reservation there?

00:46:38.561 --> 00:46:42.461
Why? It's not a special occasion.
I'm so touched.

00:46:44.001 --> 00:46:47.001
All right. My weekend is all yours.

00:46:47.601 --> 00:46:48.601
Okay, see you later.

00:46:51.001 --> 00:46:53.271
You're even going on a date
this weekend.

00:46:53.741 --> 00:46:55.781
I'm so jealous, Doctor.

00:46:56.111 --> 00:46:59.451
Director Gong is such a romantic.

00:46:59.911 --> 00:47:01.781
Romantic? Hardly.

00:47:13.381 --> 00:47:16.881
If you ever need someone
to confide in,

00:47:17.181 --> 00:47:18.181
there's always me.

00:47:19.521 --> 00:47:22.521
You know, don't you?

00:47:23.151 --> 00:47:27.591
Yes. I must confess, I'm the traitor
who helped Director Yang.

00:47:28.231 --> 00:47:30.261
Gosh, why would you do that?

00:47:31.431 --> 00:47:35.471
I don't like being left behind
by everyone either.

00:47:35.731 --> 00:47:40.101
Oh man, what am I going to do?
If Seong Mi finds out, I'm dead.

00:47:40.371 --> 00:47:42.371
She said I finally made a decision
for the family.

00:47:42.711 --> 00:47:44.981
She's been so sweet to me lately.

00:47:45.411 --> 00:47:49.081
Just think of it as going back
to your old self.

00:47:49.481 --> 00:47:51.521
It's not like you two have
always gotten along.

00:47:51.951 --> 00:47:53.351
You'll get used to it
again in no time.

00:47:54.081 --> 00:47:55.451
But what if...

00:47:56.051 --> 00:47:59.761
this causes bigger problems
for our families?

00:48:00.721 --> 00:48:04.931
Eun Bin sees Woojae as a brother,
so that won't be an issue.

00:48:05.161 --> 00:48:08.601
And Yang Dong Suk quit the clinic
to open her own shop.

00:48:09.271 --> 00:48:10.271
Really?

00:48:10.331 --> 00:48:14.041
Right. So there's no way you two
will run into each other.

00:48:14.371 --> 00:48:15.871
What's there to get
tangled up about?

00:48:16.541 --> 00:48:18.741
Right. I hope you're right.

00:48:19.541 --> 00:48:20.711
I can't believe you.

00:48:21.351 --> 00:48:23.011
- Gosh...
- Why are you snapping at me?

00:48:37.691 --> 00:48:38.701
Want me to pour you one?

00:48:39.031 --> 00:48:40.061
I'm good.

00:48:40.801 --> 00:48:42.531
What were you doing there earlier?

00:48:43.001 --> 00:48:44.901
Did you go eat way out there
because you were trying to avoid me?

00:48:45.341 --> 00:48:46.341
That's not it.

00:48:46.701 --> 00:48:49.111
My dad offered me a store,
so I went to look at it.

00:48:49.541 --> 00:48:50.541
A store?

00:48:50.611 --> 00:48:53.641
Yes. He's setting me up
so I don't have to live beaten down.

00:48:55.751 --> 00:48:56.751
Good for you.

00:48:57.451 --> 00:48:58.821
You'll be great at it.

00:49:00.081 --> 00:49:01.351
You've got the guts for it.

00:49:02.321 --> 00:49:03.621
Why are you all dressed up?

00:49:04.651 --> 00:49:05.891
Did you go on a blind date
or something?

00:49:07.161 --> 00:49:10.191
We're not even divorced yet.
What blind date? I had an interview.

00:49:10.261 --> 00:49:12.001
Why? Do I look good?

00:49:15.371 --> 00:49:17.801
I'm sorry for making you move out.

00:49:18.641 --> 00:49:20.241
It must be hard leaving a home
you've grown attached to.

00:49:21.441 --> 00:49:23.341
Hey, why are you being so nice
all of a sudden?

00:49:24.071 --> 00:49:25.811
Is it because you're grateful
I helped you out earlier?

00:49:26.881 --> 00:49:28.881
You're being nice because I'm moving
and you won't see me again, right?

00:49:30.711 --> 00:49:31.721
Both.

00:49:37.021 --> 00:49:38.221
Listen.

00:49:38.561 --> 00:49:41.021
Since we'll never meet again,
I can say this.

00:49:41.361 --> 00:49:44.291
Honestly, you were way, way too good
for that witch.

00:49:47.101 --> 00:49:48.101
I mean...

00:49:49.001 --> 00:49:51.871
Since we'll never meet again,
I'll be honest too.

00:49:54.001 --> 00:49:55.011
The same goes for you.

00:49:59.841 --> 00:50:01.911
Thanks for saying that.

00:50:04.181 --> 00:50:05.181
Dong Suk...

00:50:06.021 --> 00:50:07.521
When you told me
you were getting married,

00:50:09.151 --> 00:50:10.621
I wanted to stop you
more than anything.

00:50:11.291 --> 00:50:12.361
You should have.

00:50:13.761 --> 00:50:14.761
I guess I should have.

00:50:15.291 --> 00:50:17.861
I know.
It's my life's biggest regret.

00:50:18.931 --> 00:50:20.601
If I had,
none of this would have happened.

00:50:21.101 --> 00:50:22.101
Tell me about it.

00:50:23.601 --> 00:50:25.301
So this was all your fault,
Gong Dae Han.

00:50:25.471 --> 00:50:27.041
What? You're saying it's my fault?

00:50:28.971 --> 00:50:29.971
Hey, you're right.

00:50:30.511 --> 00:50:33.611
This is all my fault.
I'm the bad guy here.

00:50:35.811 --> 00:50:36.811
Pour me one too.

00:50:36.881 --> 00:50:39.381
All right. Hey,
since this is the end of the road,

00:50:39.751 --> 00:50:43.251
let's just do some day drinking
and wallow in our misery.

00:50:43.651 --> 00:50:48.021
No.
Let's curse those bastards to death.

00:50:48.231 --> 00:50:49.391
Let's bad-mouth them together.

00:50:50.491 --> 00:50:51.761
Okay, you're on!

00:50:52.161 --> 00:50:53.961
- Cheers! Bottoms up!
- Bottoms up!

00:50:59.871 --> 00:51:02.671
- One more!
- All right! Easy, easy.

00:51:03.011 --> 00:51:05.111
Excuse me, sir!
Another bottle over here, please.

00:51:13.181 --> 00:51:17.221
Director, I've sent the presentation
incorporating your feedback.

00:51:18.091 --> 00:51:20.061
Please review it
by tomorrow morning.

00:51:21.091 --> 00:51:23.191
- One more thing...
- I'm leaving for the day.

00:51:23.191 --> 00:51:24.731
I have a blind date.

00:51:29.101 --> 00:51:31.301
(Managing Director
Pacundo Ignacio de la Cruz Yang)

00:51:35.111 --> 00:51:36.941
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

00:51:38.881 --> 00:51:40.281
I was worried
we wouldn't get to meet.

00:51:40.611 --> 00:51:42.551
So I'm even more pleased
to meet you in person.

00:51:44.281 --> 00:51:47.921
So Hye told me so much about you,
I feel like I know you already.

00:51:49.291 --> 00:51:53.161
- Did she complain I'm too tough?
- Gosh, no.

00:51:53.421 --> 00:51:55.991
She said you're such a professional
and she has a lot to learn from you.

00:51:56.331 --> 00:51:58.731
Please. So Hye is great, too.

00:51:59.001 --> 00:52:02.331
We're even launching a special line
with one of her designs.

00:52:02.531 --> 00:52:06.241
- She also represents the designers.
- Really?

00:52:07.301 --> 00:52:10.311
I'm glad to hear
she's doing so well.

00:52:46.081 --> 00:52:48.181
Shall we go get dinner?

00:52:48.651 --> 00:52:50.681
Didn't you mention a pork belly spot
you like nearby?

00:52:52.251 --> 00:52:53.751
I do, but...

00:52:54.321 --> 00:52:55.351
Why?

00:52:55.891 --> 00:52:57.491
You're not sending me off hungry,
are you?

00:52:58.791 --> 00:52:59.791
Gosh.

00:53:02.991 --> 00:53:06.031
(Saetgol Blood Sausage Specialty)

00:53:08.201 --> 00:53:09.331
Welcome.

00:53:11.231 --> 00:53:13.541
I'll get one order of blood sausage
and intestines to go, please.

00:53:13.871 --> 00:53:14.871
Sure.

00:53:16.311 --> 00:53:18.841
The woman you came here with
last time...

00:53:19.511 --> 00:53:21.241
Are you sure
she's not your girlfriend?

00:53:22.351 --> 00:53:23.381
No, she's not.

00:53:23.851 --> 00:53:25.621
You two looked so good together.

00:53:25.951 --> 00:53:28.151
You seemed to have similar tastes
in food, too.

00:53:29.021 --> 00:53:32.321
That's a really hard thing to find,
you know.

00:53:32.861 --> 00:53:34.891
Right, I suppose so.

00:53:38.031 --> 00:53:39.101
Here you are.

00:53:42.731 --> 00:53:44.301
This place must be really popular.

00:53:44.631 --> 00:53:46.041
It's packed.

00:53:47.671 --> 00:53:48.671
Here you go.

00:53:49.811 --> 00:53:51.071
I'll stick with water.

00:53:51.371 --> 00:53:52.741
Did you drive here?

00:53:53.981 --> 00:53:57.681
No, I don't really drink.
It's high in calories...

00:53:57.751 --> 00:53:59.151
and it interferes
with muscle growth.

00:53:59.621 --> 00:54:01.481
Oh, I see.

00:54:03.591 --> 00:54:04.621
Thanks.

00:54:05.491 --> 00:54:08.261
I forgot to order rice.
Would you like a bowl?

00:54:08.321 --> 00:54:10.561
No, I'm good. I don't eat carbs.

00:54:14.101 --> 00:54:17.271
- Can I get a bowl of rice, please?
- Sure.

00:54:19.171 --> 00:54:22.841
Eating rice with your meat
will really spike your blood sugar.

00:54:23.971 --> 00:54:28.111
- You're not much of a foodie.
- I like eating healthy.

00:54:30.281 --> 00:54:34.051
- So you must dislike many foods.
- Yes.

00:54:34.551 --> 00:54:37.091
I don't really like
heavily seasoned or spicy food.

00:54:37.421 --> 00:54:40.161
Intestines, blood sausage, and...

00:54:42.531 --> 00:54:43.531
chicken feet.

00:54:43.891 --> 00:54:46.731
I can't stand that stuff.
It's disgusting.

00:54:53.541 --> 00:54:56.541
My dream is to have a girlfriend
I can work out with.

00:54:57.071 --> 00:54:58.441
Do you like working out,
by any chance?

00:54:59.381 --> 00:55:03.181
The only exercise I do is breathing.

00:55:11.091 --> 00:55:14.391
The one thing that never betrays you
is muscle.

00:55:15.431 --> 00:55:19.031
Try fasted cardio first thing.
I can make a meal plan for you.

00:55:22.101 --> 00:55:26.071
But there's something
I'm really curious about.

00:55:26.371 --> 00:55:28.611
- The meal plan?
- No.

00:55:29.071 --> 00:55:30.071
I mean...

00:55:30.771 --> 00:55:34.081
Why do you keep cutting
all the fat off?

00:55:35.911 --> 00:55:38.311
This is basically a lump
of saturated fat.

00:55:38.621 --> 00:55:40.181
It's equivalent to an entire
weight-lifting set.

00:55:45.461 --> 00:55:49.431
What is he talking about?
The fat's the best part of the pork.

00:55:53.501 --> 00:55:57.731
All right, lay a pickled garlic leaf
on top of the lettuce,

00:55:58.101 --> 00:56:00.501
Add a bit of that
glistening white rice,

00:56:00.841 --> 00:56:05.511
then take a piece of pork belly,
dip it in anchovy sauce and add it.

00:56:05.541 --> 00:56:08.781
And top it with a slice of garlic
and a hot green pepper.

00:56:09.151 --> 00:56:10.951
And there you have it. Perfection.

00:56:23.231 --> 00:56:24.231
Incredible.

00:56:24.831 --> 00:56:25.831
It's killer, right?

00:56:26.131 --> 00:56:30.831
Savory juices mix with the leaves,
then the garlic and pepper's kick...

00:56:30.901 --> 00:56:35.171
spreads through your mouth, then,
the anchovy sauce's rich umami hits.

00:56:35.241 --> 00:56:37.241
That's when you wash it down
with a shot of soju.

00:56:45.721 --> 00:56:49.221
- That's the perfect finish.
- Ju Ah.

00:56:50.051 --> 00:56:51.051
Yes?

00:56:52.261 --> 00:56:53.391
Who are you talking to?

00:57:00.831 --> 00:57:01.871
Good question.

00:57:02.801 --> 00:57:03.971
Where did he go?

00:57:04.331 --> 00:57:05.541
You've had too much to drink.

00:57:06.101 --> 00:57:07.101
Let's call it a night.

00:57:09.441 --> 00:57:12.141
Excuse me, can I get another
bottle of soju, please?

00:57:20.251 --> 00:57:21.251
Well then.

00:57:30.031 --> 00:57:32.801
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

00:57:35.971 --> 00:57:39.801
Why on earth would you
give that witch money?

00:57:40.341 --> 00:57:41.501
Go get it back. Right now.

00:57:41.871 --> 00:57:43.241
Hey, just drop it.

00:57:44.441 --> 00:57:48.181
Your ex-husband doesn't have a dime.
How can she live if she's broke too?

00:57:48.381 --> 00:57:49.451
Poor thing.

00:57:50.251 --> 00:57:51.511
She has it rough.

00:57:51.951 --> 00:57:54.621
Oh, please.
You married her out of pity, right?

00:57:55.051 --> 00:57:57.351
Your protective instincts kicked in,
or something.

00:57:59.021 --> 00:58:02.561
You've always been a softie,
Dae Han.

00:58:02.961 --> 00:58:06.261
You just mistook it for love.

00:58:07.161 --> 00:58:08.531
I guess you could be right.

00:58:10.131 --> 00:58:11.371
She was like a lost,

00:58:12.071 --> 00:58:13.701
pitiful little puppy.

00:58:14.101 --> 00:58:15.101
A puppy?

00:58:16.811 --> 00:58:18.211
So you married her
because she was cute.

00:58:20.041 --> 00:58:21.141
Then again...

00:58:21.411 --> 00:58:24.451
She's pretty, so of course
Ji Hu's dad fell for her.

00:58:25.981 --> 00:58:29.251
Now that I'm old and ugly,

00:58:30.691 --> 00:58:33.591
he went running to her,
heart and soul.

00:58:36.261 --> 00:58:37.261
Dong Suk.

00:58:38.961 --> 00:58:40.161
You're beautiful.

00:58:41.001 --> 00:58:42.031
As if.

00:58:42.971 --> 00:58:45.541
What is with you... Hey.

00:58:45.871 --> 00:58:48.041
You were the prettiest girl
in all of Onjeong.

00:58:48.401 --> 00:58:50.611
Back when you were in high school,

00:58:51.141 --> 00:58:52.881
all those guys would hang out
in front of your school...

00:58:52.941 --> 00:58:57.381
lined up every day
just hoping to see you.

00:58:57.851 --> 00:59:00.881
I was worried about you at night,
so I would wait at the study hall...

00:59:00.951 --> 00:59:03.351
and walk you home.
Don't you remember?

00:59:04.851 --> 00:59:06.521
That was a long time ago.

00:59:07.091 --> 00:59:08.731
Not anymore.

00:59:10.661 --> 00:59:11.961
You're still beautiful.

00:59:14.361 --> 00:59:15.431
I'm telling you, you are.

00:59:16.971 --> 00:59:18.031
Back then...

00:59:19.441 --> 00:59:20.441
and now.

00:59:25.011 --> 00:59:26.181
Thanks.

00:59:27.241 --> 00:59:29.051
Hey, don't smile.

00:59:29.651 --> 00:59:33.021
Don't smile.
You're even prettier when you do.

00:59:33.821 --> 00:59:35.421
Oh, stop it.

00:59:36.291 --> 00:59:37.521
Your eyes are beautiful.

00:59:38.521 --> 00:59:39.761
Your nose is beautiful.

00:59:42.361 --> 00:59:43.691
And your lips are beautiful.

01:00:35.881 --> 01:00:37.711
Over here!

01:00:39.321 --> 01:00:41.351
Why won't any taxis stop?

01:01:00.471 --> 01:01:01.471
You're awake?

01:01:04.741 --> 01:01:05.881
I'm losing my mind.

01:01:06.681 --> 01:01:09.281
Why do I keep thinking about him?

01:01:09.911 --> 01:01:10.911
Why?

01:01:18.051 --> 01:01:19.561
Yang Hyun Bin.

01:01:22.991 --> 01:01:27.761
This is ridiculous.
Am I hearing things now?

01:01:36.371 --> 01:01:39.611
Gosh, why does it keep running away?

01:01:44.081 --> 01:01:46.221
Ding-dong.

01:01:47.221 --> 01:01:49.891
Hey, Yang Hyun Bin, get out here!

01:01:50.421 --> 01:01:52.791
- Oh my!
- Ms. Gong Ju Ah?

01:01:56.931 --> 01:01:57.991
Are you okay?

01:01:59.931 --> 01:02:02.371
Gosh. You're really...

01:02:02.701 --> 01:02:05.401
- unbelievable, you know that?
- What?

01:02:06.371 --> 01:02:07.401
Seriously.

01:02:12.711 --> 01:02:13.711
I'm sorry.

01:02:14.911 --> 01:02:17.011
- Get inside.
- Let go...

01:02:28.621 --> 01:02:29.891
Have you been drinking?

01:02:30.791 --> 01:02:31.991
Yes. So what if I have?

01:02:32.831 --> 01:02:34.261
You jerk.

01:02:34.561 --> 01:02:35.601
What?

01:02:36.101 --> 01:02:39.071
- A jerk?
- You said you missed me, right?

01:02:39.401 --> 01:02:42.471
That you still have feelings for me.
That it was destiny.

01:02:43.341 --> 01:02:48.281
So what's this? We can't be friends?
I'm not allowed to be nice to you?

01:02:48.611 --> 01:02:49.611
Gosh.

01:02:50.151 --> 01:02:52.951
But then why were you so nice to me?

01:02:53.151 --> 01:02:55.181
Why can't I stop thinking about you?

01:02:55.821 --> 01:02:58.791
If you were going to be this way,
why'd you even come back to Korea?

01:03:00.221 --> 01:03:02.391
Why did you have to show up
in my life again?

01:03:05.391 --> 01:03:06.431
Are you laughing?

01:03:07.261 --> 01:03:09.371
What's so funny?

01:03:12.171 --> 01:03:13.171
Because I'm grateful.

01:03:15.741 --> 01:03:17.111
I missed you so much,

01:03:18.641 --> 01:03:19.841
and here you are.

01:03:20.811 --> 01:03:22.111
I'm just so happy.

01:03:39.601 --> 01:03:41.201
I'm going home.

01:04:25.511 --> 01:04:28.011
(Recipe For Love)

01:04:28.081 --> 01:04:30.351
Shall I report on their progress?

01:04:30.411 --> 01:04:34.121
- I'll come up with the plan.
- He'll surely ask her out today.

01:04:34.481 --> 01:04:36.951
- As of today, we're official.
- You're unbelievable.

01:04:37.191 --> 01:04:39.091
My mom didn't come home last night.

01:04:39.591 --> 01:04:40.961
Did anyone
around the neighborhood notice me?

01:04:40.961 --> 01:04:42.161
Dong Suk!

01:04:42.221 --> 01:04:43.991
Did they see me getting drunk
and going into a motel?

01:04:45.231 --> 01:04:46.961
Who'd you hear that from?

01:04:48.061 --> 01:04:49.631
All that's left is
a sweet fragrance.

01:04:50.501 --> 01:04:51.971
Especially when I'm with you,

01:04:52.801 --> 01:04:54.971
I will live as a woman
who never fades.

01:05:00.202 --> 01:05:02.202
Dramaday.me